		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Poe Ballantine</span></strong> does <em>not</em> need bifocals, he says, as he slides his glasses to the tip of his nose to read. He is the author of the true-crime book <em>Love and Terror on the Howling Plains of Nowhere</em>, due out in 2012, and the subject of the documentary <em>Poe Ballantine, A Writer in America</em> (copies of which can be purchased for $13.99, shipping included, from Al Saperstein, P.O. Box 111, Earleton, Florida, 32631). He lives in Chadron, Nebraska.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
